description: Prime Minister Gabriel Attal unveiled a plan to cut French unemployment benefits in a bid to advance President Emmanuel Macron’s economic reforms.
title: France to Trim Benefits for Jobless as Debt Pressure Mounts

description: France’s far-right National Rally is extending its lead against President Emmanuel Macron’s party in European elections to be held in two weeks, according to an Elabe poll for La Tribune and BFM TV.
title: French Far-Right Seen Trouncing Macron’s Party in EU Elections

description: The Conservative Party said it would require mandatory national service for every 18-year-old Briton by the end of the next Parliament, a striking political gamble as UK Prime Minister Rishi Sunak sets out his six-week campaign messaging ahead of the July election.
title: Sunak Pledges Mandatory National Service in UK Election Gambit

description: Burkina Faso will allow junta leader Ibrahim Traore to contest the next presidential election, becoming the second West African nation under military control to delay a return to civilian rule.
title: Burkina Faso Military Leader Set to Stay in Power Until 2029

description: A Russian gliding bomb struck a home-improvement superstore in Kharkiv on Saturday, killing at least two people and igniting a fast-moving blaze.
title: Russian Bombs Wound Dozens at Hypermarket in Ukraine’s Kharkiv

description: Ukraine made a drone strike this week at a tactical military target in Russia’s Krasnodar region, according to a person within the Ukrainian intelligence community.
title: Ukraine Says It Struck Anti-Missile Defense Radar in Russia

description: The murder of two US missionaries in Haiti this week by powerful gangs underscores the urgent need to deploy an international security force to the troubled Caribbean nation, the US Department of State said.
title: US Calls for Rapid Deployment to Haiti After Missionaries Killed

description: President Vladimir Putin urged the heads of manufacturers of military hardware to ramp up output and make Russia’s war economy more effective.
title: Putin Meets Military Plant Chiefs, Asks to Speed Up War Economy

description: China’s engagement in the global system of commerce was roundly criticized by Group of Seven finance chiefs in a show of unity accompanied by a threat of further escalation.
title: China Slammed in G-7 Show of Unity Threatening Trade Escalation

description: South Africa’s political parties began winding up their campaigns ahead of next week’s pivotal elections, with the ruling African National Congress and the leftist Economic Freedom Fighters staging huge rallies that highlighted their mass appeal.
title: South African Parties Wind Up Campaigns Ahead of Pivotal Vote

description: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said the US won’t sign an agreement to finalize a still-pending global tax deal until India and China agree to key unresolved issues.
title: Yellen Says US Isn’t Ready to Sign Pending Global Tax Agreement

description: Ukrainian Finance Minister Serhiy Marchenko said he’s pleased with how Group of Seven talks have advanced on funding aid via profits gleaned from Russian assets.
title: Ukraine Satisfied on G-7 Asset Plan Progress, Finance Chief Says

description: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said the outlook for higher interest rates over the long haul makes it tougher to contain US borrowing needs, heightening the importance of boosting revenue in negotiations with Republican lawmakers.
title: Yellen Says Higher Path for Rates Boosts Need to Lift Revenue

description: UK Chancellor of the Exchequer Jeremy Hunt warned Western allies not to “creep back into protectionism” as the US and European Union prepare new trade barriers against goods from China.
title: UK’s Chancellor Warns Allies Against Creep Back to Protectionism

description: NATO members should ease their prohibitions on using weapons they supply to Ukraine to strike military targets in Russia, the alliance’s secretary-general said in an interview with The Economist.
title: NATO Chief Backs Use of Western Weapons to Hit Russian Targets

description: Chancellor of the Exchequer Jeremy Hunt said he’s determined to fight for his seat in the UK Parliament even though the ruling Conservative Party is trailing in polls and other ministers are stepping aside.
title: UK Chancellor Will Fight for Seat in Election Despite Poll Gap

description: Italy says it will resume funding the UN’s Palestinian aid agency, UNRWA, and signaled support for an Arab-led peacekeeping mission in Gaza once the Israel-Hamas war ends.
title: Italy Resumes UNRWA Funding, Backs Arab-Led Gaza Peace Mission

description: More than 48,000 hopefuls have submitted applications for Thailand’s upcoming Senate race, a number that the country’s election body says falls below expectations.
title: Thai Senate Race Attracts Fewer Applicants Than Anticipated

description: Zambian economic growth is expected to recover next year from the effects of the worst drought in at least four decades, Secretary to the Treasury Felix Nkulukusa said.
title: Zambia Economic Growth to Rebound in 2025, Finance Ministry Says

description: China said a deputy head of the State Tobacco Monopoly Administration is under investigation by the anti-graft agency for “serious violations” of the law, the latest senior government official to be probed for alleged wrongdoing.
title: China’s Anti-Graft Agency Probes State Tobacco Deputy Head

description: In the 1990s, Tony Blair and Gordon Brown’s New Labour courted UK business in efforts that became known as the “prawn cocktail offensive” — a reference to the seafood appetizer that in times gone by was known for featuring at posh lunches.
title: The Next UK Prime Minister Faces a Long Wish List From CEOs

description: French President Emmanuel Macron heads to Germany for a three-day state visit on Sunday that will test the ability of the European Union’s core couple to set the bloc’s agenda just two weeks before potentially bruising elections.
title: Macron Visit to Test Franco-German Relationship: What to Watch

description: China has concluded expansive military exercises around Taiwan, held in the wake of Lai Ching-te’s inauguration as the island’s president.
title: China Ends Its Biggest Military Drills Around Taiwan in a Year

description: Rishi Sunak gave his most senior ministers little more than an hour’s notice of what he was about to tell the country and had already told King Charles III, that he had decided to call a snap UK general election for July 4.
title: How Sunak’s Small Circle Forged Vote Plan That Shocked Cabinet

description: As investigators closed in on their biggest target of Kazakhstan’s anti-corruption campaign, they uncovered clues in Kairat Satybaldyuly’s meticulous notes.
title: Secret Billionaire Unmasked in Kazakh Fraud Hunt Caused by Riots

description: Special counsel Jack Smith asked for a court order forbidding Donald Trump from continuing to claim that FBI agents were authorized to kill him when they searched Mar-o-Lago last year for classified documents.
title: Smith Seeks Trump Gag Order Over False FBI Assassination Theory

description: Wealthy, democratic and strategically located off the Chinese coast, Taiwan has long been the most volatile issue between the US and China. Both sides have avoided serious conflict by leaving unsettled the question of who actually owns the island. But it’s becoming harder to avoid as China’s military ratchets up exercises near what President Xi Jinping views as his country’s lost territory. Standing in the way are the US Pacific Fleet and Taiwanese voters, who have emphatically rejected closer t
title: Why Taiwan’s Status Risks Igniting a US-China Clash

description: Two key opposition parties are hailing their alliance in India’s capital Delhi, and hoping they can deny Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s and his party a third consecutive clean sweep of the region in the ongoing elections.
title: Opposition Rivals Turned Allies Hope to Unseat Modi In Delhi
